summary: Short story [[MORE]] I once came across a little girl at the station. What was strikingly unusual about her was that she was by...
body:
Short story

I once came across a little girl at the station. What was strikingly unusual about her was that she was by herself. I asked her what she was doing alone. She said she was waiting for her train to arrive.


“What time does your train leave?” I asked.

“5:45,” she replied.


I wanted to stay until she got on her train, but I had my own to catch as well.


“Will you be alright on your own?”

“Yes. My train will arrive very soon.”


I hurriedly made my way to my platform. 6:35. Ah, just in time. As I was getting on my train, doors closing right behind me, I thought about the little girl.


5:45, she said.


The lonely girl waiting for a train that’s already left.
